## 📂 Module 4.1: Data Reading from a File

In this stage, an external dataset (`Dataset.xlsx`) was imported into the MATLAB environment. The column names (features) were renamed for better clarity, and the basic structure of the data was inspected.

### 🛠️ MATLAB Code Content & Explanations

The following script clears the workspace, reads the data from the Excel file as a table format, and structures it entirely in English:

```matlab
clc;
clear;
close all;

filename = 'Dataset.xlsx';                                                                    % File name of the dataset
dataLines = readtable(filename);                                                              % Reading data from the Excel file into a table format

dataLines.Properties.VariableNames = {'Pressure', 'Humidity', 'Temperature', 'Weather', 'Density'}; % Renaming and defining column names (features) for clarity

disp("Reading process completed successfully.");                                              % Displaying an informational message in the console
head(dataLines, 10);                                                                          % Previewing the first 10 rows of the dataset

[rowCount, columnCount] = size(dataLines);                                                    % Calculating the dimensions (number of rows and columns)
fprintf("Our data consists of %d rows and %d columns.\n", rowCount, columnCount);

